omics from claremont mckenna college where he was elected to phi beta kappa and was an ncaa allamerican tennis player zinnatalayacapcom david p aidi partner partner mr aidi has extensive experience in alternative credit investing and has deep experience executing specialty finance and corporate transactions prior to joining atalaya mr aidi was the portfolio manager in charge of the direct lending group and a member of the investment committee at magnetar capital llc prior to magnetar mr aidi was a corporate analyst at highbridgezwirn focused on private lending and special opportunities investments where he worked closely with mr zinn mr aidi began his career at merrill lynch holding positions within the high yield capital markets group as well as the telecommunications media and technology investment banking group mr aidi earned a bs in business administration summa cum laude from the stern school of business at new york university and is a current member of the nyu young alumni leadership council aidiatalayacapcom raymond s chan partner partner mr chan has extensive experience in originating and investing in a range of financial assets focused on specialty finance transactions prior to joining atalaya mr chan was a partner and cofounder of ttm capital llc an investment firm focused on acquiring and lending against portfolios of financial and other assets prior to ttm mr chan was a managing director and cohead of the assets group at db zwirn  co previously mr chan was a member of the principal transaction and principal finance teams at lehman brothers and worked on numerous securitizations across multiple asset classes at salomon brothers mr chan began his career as a consultant at price waterhouse followed by an internal consulting and operations roles at lehman brothers mr chan received a ba in economics and political science from columbia university chanatalayacapcom robert m flowers partner partner mr flowers brings over  years of investment experience as a team leader portfolio manager trader originator and analyst he has deep experience in structured finance and related sectors supported by a strong background in credit and leverage finance mr flowers was a cofounder and partner of ttm capital llc an investment firm focused on acquiring and lending against portfolios of financial and other assets prior to ttm mr flowers was a managing director and cohead of the assets group at db zwirn  co previously mr flowers was an executive vice president at ppm america inc where he founded and led the structured finance and cdo management group mr flowers began his career in credit and leverage finance investing at alliance capital management and connecticut national bank mr flowers earned a ba in business economics at university of california at santa barbara and an mba in finance at columbia university flowersatalayacapcom drew c phillips partner  chief operating officer partner  chief operating officer mr phillips has broad management and financial services experience working with institutional investors and global financial institutions mr phillips joined atalaya from tiger bay advisors a boutique asset management consultancy he cofounded focused on driving operational efficiency agility and scale prior to tiger bay mr phillips has served as the manager of the fund and client legal group at bridgewater associates as well as the assistant general counsel  director of new products at the rohatyn group mr phillips was also a vicepresident for the americas at the bank of tokyomitsubishi and an associate at the law firm cadwalader wickersham  taft mr phillips earned his ba degree in economics from columbia university his jd from georgetown university law center and is the president of the board of directors of the children’s cancer and blood foundation the largest and oldest charitable organization in the united states dedicated to the care of children suffering from blood diseases and cancers phillipsatalayacapcom joshua d ufberg pa